	file2e := &embedded.EmbeddedFile{
		Filename:    `templates/code_signing/index.html`,
		FileModTime: time.Unix(1481718967, 0),
		Content:     string("<div class=\"code-signing\" ng-controller=\"CodeSigningController as codeSigningCtrl\"><p class=\"progress-indicator\" progress-model=\"codeSigningCtrl.loadSupportedPlatforms\"></p><div ng-if=\"codeSigningCtrl.loadSupportedPlatforms.isIdle\"><div ng-if=\"!codeSigningCtrl.isSupportedPlatform('xamarin') && codeSigningCtrl.isSupportedPlatform('ios')\"><section><h2>Psst... You should use our friendly neighborhood iOS Code Signing Doctor!</h2><p>After running a simple command... <pre><code>bash -l -c \"$(curl -sfL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/bitrise-tools/codesigndoc/master/_scripts/install_wrap.sh)\"</code></pre>...you'll have all the code signing files (.p12 Identity file including the Certificate and Private Key, and the required Provisioning Profiles), ready for upload. <a href='http://devcenter.bitrise.io/docs/provprofile-cert-export#section-use-our-codesigndoc-tool-to-get-your-code-signing-files' target=\"_blank\">More info!</a></p></section><section><p>Don't forget to add the Certificate and Provisioning Profile Installer step to your workflow to make code signing work for your project!</p></section></div><section ng-if=\"codeSigningCtrl.isSupportedPlatform('xamarin')\"><h2>Hey, let me help with code signing!</h2><p>We've prepared a handy guide to help you with the signing of your Xamarin app, because we're looking out for you.  And don't worry, it's not that long. Hit the purple button on the right to teleport you to the tutorial! <a href='http://devcenter.bitrise.io/v1.0/docs/getting-started-with-xamarin-on-bitrise#section-code-signing' target=\"_blank\">Check tutorial</a></p></section><section ng-if=\"!codeSigningCtrl.isSupportedPlatform('xamarin') && codeSigningCtrl.isSupportedPlatform('android')\"><h2>Hey, let me help with code signing!</h2><p>We've prepared a handy guide to help you with the signing of your Android app. Be glad that it's not as painful as for the iOS folks, but still, we like to look out for you. Hit the purple button on the right to teleport you to the tutorial! <a href='https://bitrise-io.github.io/devcenter/tutorials/create-signed-apk-on-bitrise/' target=\"_blank\">Check tutorial</a></p></section><div ng-if=\"codeSigningCtrl.isSupportedPlatform('xamarin') || codeSigningCtrl.isSupportedPlatform('ios')\"><section class=\"provisioning-profile\" ng-controller=\"ProvProfileController as provProfileCtrl\"><header>Provisioning Profile</header><article><section ng-repeat=\"provProfile in provProfileCtrl.provProfiles\"><h2><span>Filename: </span><span ng-bind=\"provProfile | displayNameForProvProfile\"></span></h2><p class=\"progress-indicator\" ng-if=\"provProfile == provProfileCtrl.selectedProvProfile\" progress-model=\"provProfileCtrl.provProfileActionProgress\"></p><div ng-if=\"!provProfileCtrl.provProfileActionProgress.isInProgress\"><button ng-click=\"provProfileCtrl.downloadProvProfile(provProfile)\">Download</button><button ng-click=\"provProfileCtrl.deleteProvProfile(provProfile)\">Delete</button></div></section><section class=\"actions\"><div ng-if=\"!provProfileCtrl.isAddMode\"><button class=\"add\" ng-click=\"provProfileCtrl.addProvProfileSelected()\">+ Add Provisioning Profile</button><button class=\"delete\" ng-click=\"provProfileCtrl.deleteAllProvProfilesSelected()\">Delete all</button></div><div ng-if=\"provProfileCtrl.isAddMode && provProfileCtrl.provProfiles.length > 1\"><p>Upload the Provisioning Profile:</p><p class=\"progress-indicator\" progress-model=\"provProfileCtrl.uploadProvProfileProgress\"></p><file-uploader onupload=\"provProfileCtrl.uploadProvProfile()\">Click here or Drag&Drop to upload</file-uploader></div></section></article></section><section class=\"certificate\"></section></div><section class=\"android-keystore-generic-file\"></section></div></div>"),
	}
